    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "Global sensitivity analysis for non-cannulated pedicle screw FEA ensemble",
    "description": "A Sobol variance-based global sensitivity analysis (N=4096 quasi-random LHS samples) was conducted varying cortical bone modulus (E_cortical: 12–22 GPa), cancellous bone modulus (E_cancellous: 0.1–1.5 GPa), screw-bone interface friction coefficient (mu: 0.2–0.6), and titanium alloy yield strength (sigma_y: 880–970 MPa). Construct stiffness QoI showed dominant first-order sensitivity to E_cortical (S1=0.61) and mu (S1=0.22); force at 40 mm displacement was dominated by sigma_y (S1=0.54) and E_cortical (S1=0.29). Total-order indices confirmed negligible higher-order interactions (ST-S1 < 0.05 for all factors), validating the linearity assumptions used in the UQ propagation step.",
    "method": "Sobol variance-based global sensitivity (Saltelli 2010 estimator)",
    "dominantFactors": [
      "cortical bone modulus",
      "screw-bone friction coefficient",
      "titanium yield strength"
    ],
    "sampleSize": 4096
  },
  "hasContextOfUse": {
