      "rationale": "Linear elastic isotropic material model adopted for Ti-6Al-4V rod and screw below yield; bilinear isotropic hardening (tangent modulus 1.1 GPa) beyond yield. UHMWPE block modeled as linear elastic (E=0.95 GPa, nu=0.46) consistent with published material characterization. Frictional contact (Coulomb, mu=0.35) at screw-block interface; bonded contact at rod-screw interface per experimental fixture. Model form selection justified by published literature (Nagaraja 2019, Imanishi 2021) and sensitivity analysis confirming negligible sensitivity to viscoelastic UHMWPE creep at 5 mm/min loading rate. Continuum assumption valid at 0.5 mm element size relative to grain size ~10 µm.",
