      "rationale": "The three QoIs (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are the primary metrics specified in ASTM F1717-15 and directly relevant to the 510(k) submission decision criteria. Stiffness characterises elastic load transfer to adjacent vertebrae; yield force determines onset of permanent deformation; force at 40 mm represents ultimate load-bearing capacity. Clinical relevance: construct stiffness correlates with adjacent segment load redistribution (Rohlmann 2009); yield force threshold is the basis for fatigue life prediction. QoI selection reviewed and approved by clinical advisory panel (meeting minutes archived 2023-09-14).",
