        "type": "OffsetRationale",
        "name": "Offset rationale for Test conditions shortfall (Gradation 3 vs. required 4)",
        "refersToFactor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/factor/test-conditions",
        "justification": "The Test conditions factor achieves Gradation 3 (single loading rate, single environmental condition) against the required Gradation 4 for MRL 5. This shortfall is accepted on three grounds: (1) The COU operating envelope is explicitly bounded to the ASTM F1717-15 standard test condition (5 mm/min, 23°C), so multi-condition coverage is not required for the intended regulatory use; (2) the Sobol sensitivity analysis assigns a first-order index S1 < 0.02 to loading rate for all three QoIs, confirming that rate-dependent effects are negligible within the operating envelope; (3) all three QoIs satisfy the quantitative acceptance criteria with substantial margin (maximum E/uval = 1.21 vs. threshold 1.96), providing additional confidence that the single-condition validation is sufficient to support the regulatory claim. No compensating factor credit is claimed; the shortfall is accepted on the basis of COU restriction and demonstrated insensitivity."
      },
